content: User Friendly CORS           U.S. DEPARTMENT OF COMMERCE   National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration   National Ocean Service Version 2.18 - October 31, 2003   This utility allows you to obtain a specific block of Global Positioning System (GPS)                data for a continously operating reference station (CORS) contained in the network of GPS                sites managed by the National Geodetic Survey. The GPS data will be in "receiver independent exchange" (RINEX) format, version 2.   Questions or Comments?  Send email to                 cors@ngs.noaa.gov ** NOTE: Whenever possible, please use the new Problem/Comment form below or at the bottom  of the following page to report problems. This means you can move around various dates, display by week, by month, etc, however is convenient for you, and the schedule you see is always the most current.  The links below will jump you directly to each month, but once there you can jump to whatever dates you want to see.   Beamtime calendars for dates in the past will remain in Adobe Acrobat PDF format.   Beamtime shifts are allocated by the ALS in 8-hour increments. We typically schedule running shifts for 8am - 8pm, and from 8pm - 8am the next day (12 hours counts as 1.5 allocated shifts), but we are flexible and want to match you actual time needs as closely as possible.
